# MarkdownScript Demo

This is a demonstration of **MarkdownScript** (.mdsc) - Markdown with embedded JavaScript!

## Variable Definition

:::script{lang="js"}
const products = [
  { name: "Widget A", price: 29.99, stock: 150 },
  { name: "Widget B", price: 49.99, stock: 75 },
  { name: "Widget C", price: 19.99, stock: 200 },
];

const total = products.reduce((sum, p) => sum + p.price * p.stock, 0);
const formatter = new Intl.NumberFormat('de-DE', { style: 'currency', currency: 'EUR' });
:::

## Product List

:::script:output{lang="js"}
return products.map(p => `- **${p.name}**: ${formatter.format(p.price)} (${p.stock} in stock)`).join('\n');
:::

## Summary

:::script:output{lang="js"}
return `> **Total Inventory Value:** ${formatter.format(total)}`;
:::

## Dynamic Date

:::script:output{lang="js"}
const now = new Date();
const options = { weekday: 'long', year: 'numeric', month: 'long', day: 'numeric' };
return `*Generated on: ${now.toLocaleDateString('de-DE', options)}*`;
:::

